<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-22-0371 </DOCNO><TEXT>This paper explores the many factors which must be considered when evaluatingthe merits of installing small privately-owned wind turbines in the UKwhen these are to operate in association with the national electricalnetwork. The observations reported are made consequent to The EnergyAct 1983 becoming law, and to publication by the Area Supply Boards ofthe tariff structures agreed with the Electricity Council to apply accordingto the relevant terms of that Act.</TEXT></DOC>